{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Bz45oUTA9j3zNUJz19VZrF","type":"tool_result","content":"1700\t    `username` (LEFT JOIN `player_profiles`, null when absent), `wallet`,\n1701\t    `amountLamports`, `side`, `isWinner`, `payoutLamports`, `createdAt`,\n1702\t    `settledAt`. Distinct from the user-detail `PeekGameEntryRow` because\n1703\t    the round-detail page renders participants (so it needs identity\n1704\t    columns) instead of a single user's recent entries.\n1705\t  - `PeekRoundTransactionRow` — same identity treatment for the\n1706\t    `transactions` join (txType, amountLamports, txSig, createdAt).\n1707\t  - `PeekRoundDetail` — discriminated union on `game`. The\n1708\t    `flipyou`/`potshot` branch carries `PeekRoundRow`; the `closecall`\n1709\t    branch carries `PeekCloseCallRoundRow`. Entries + transactions are\n1710\t    shared shapes since both tables produce the same operator surface.\n1711\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅, `pnpm test\n1712\t  --run` ✅ (334/334, no regressions). The page + dedicated round-detail\n1713\t  query/page tests are the next two FR-8 items.\n1714\t## Iteration 36 — 2026-04-25T13:25:30Z — OK\n1715\t- **Log**: iteration-036.log\n1716\t\n1717\t\n1718\t\n1719\t\n1720\t## Iteration 37 — 2026-04-25\n1721\t\n1722\t- FR-8 frontend: `/games/[game]/rounds/[roundId]` detail page. Reads\n1723\t  `getRoundDetail({ game, roundId })` from iteration 36 and renders three\n1724\t  sections so an operator can audit the full round lifecycle in one place:\n1725\t  round summary, entries, and transactions.\n1726\t- New `peek/app/games/[game]/rounds/[roundId]/page.tsx`:\n1727\t  - Validates `[game]` against `PEEK_GAME_IDS` and `notFound()`s out-of-band\n1728\t    values (e.g. `crash`) before any DB call. Same access path as\n1729\t    `/games/[game]`: `getPeekActorContext` + `isRouteAllowedForRole` so an\n1730\t    unknown role gets the read-only access-denied alert without leaking the\n1731\t    round.\n1732\t  - When the query returns `null` for an unknown round PDA the page calls\n1733\t    `notFound()`. When the query throws, the page renders an inline\n1734\t    `role=\"alert\"` so a transient DB failure doesn't nuke the route — same\n1735\t    pattern the per-game list page uses.\n1736\t  - Breadcrumb: `← Games · [Game]` with two `Link`s back to `/games` and\n1737\t    `/games/[game]` so an operator can jump back to either level without\n1738\t    losing their place.\n1739\t- Round summary block:\n1740\t  - FlipYou + Pot Shot branch: `RoundSummary` renders every `PeekRoundRow`\n1741\t    field from FR-8 (phase, match id, pda, creator, amount lamports, target\n1742\t    slot, settle attempts, result side, winner, settle tx, created/updated/\n1743\t    settled timestamps). Phase reuses the existing\n1744\t    `phaseTone(PeekRoundPhase)` mapping so settled/expired/settling/locked\n1745\t    visually match the `/games/[game]` list table.\n1746\t  - Close Call branch: `CloseCallSummary` renders every\n1747\t    `PeekCloseCallRoundRow` field (phase, outcome, round id, pda, open price\n1748\t    + Pyth `expo` sublabel, close price, green/red pools, total fee, settle\n1749\t    tx, created/settled). Outcome + phase render as side-by-side\n1750\t    `StatusChip`s with the same tones as `closecall-rounds-table` so a\n1751\t    `refunded`+`refund` round pops the same way it does in the list.\n1752\t  - Layout is a `<dl>` grid with `auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr)` columns so\n1753\t    the summary collapses cleanly on narrow viewports without needing a\n1754\t    media-query stylesheet.\n1755\t  - Long pubkeys (pda, creator, winner, settle_tx, match id, round id, tx\n1756\t    sig, wallet) truncate via the existing `truncate()` helper and keep the\n1757\t    full string in `title=` for hover audit. Lamport / u64 values format\n1758\t    with thousands separators while preserving the literal `\"0\"` for\n1759\t    measured zeros (FR-4).\n1760\t- Entries section (`EntriesTable` over `PeekRoundEntryRow`):\n1761\t  - Columns: created, user, wallet, amount lamports (right-aligned), side,\n1762\t    winner, payout lamports (right-aligned), settled. The `user` cell\n1763\t    becomes a `Link` to `/users/[userId]` (FR-6 drill-down) showing\n1764\t    `username` when `player_profiles` had a row, falling back to a\n1765\t    truncated user id with the full id in `title=`.\n1766\t  - `isWinner` renders as `yes`/`no`/`—` so an operator can scan winners\n1767\t    quickly. Lamport zeros stay as `\"0\"` (measured zero), but null\n1768\t    settledAt / null side render `—` to avoid mistaking sparse data for a\n1769\t    measured outcome.\n1770\t  - Sparse state explains the absence operationally — \"No entries recorded\n1771\t    for this round\" + \"the `game_entries` table has no rows joined to this\n1772\t    round PDA. This is normal for rounds that were created but never\n1773\t    joined.\" — matching the FR-3 empty-state convention used elsewhere in\n1774\t    `peek`.\n1775\t- Transactions section (`TransactionsTable` over\n1776\t  `PeekRoundTransactionRow`):\n1777\t  - Columns: created, type (StatusChip), user (Link or `—`), wallet,\n1778\t    amount lamports (right-aligned), tx signature (mono + truncated +\n1779\t    `title=`). User column is null when the chain row has no resolved\n1780\t    `user_id` so the table doesn't fabricate a user link.\n1781\t  - Sparse state references the FR-8 stuck-state filter on\n1782\t    `/games/[game]` (\"settled rounds without transaction rows are an\n1783\t    attention state surfaced by the stuck-state filters\") so an operator\n1784\t    arriving from a stuck-state filter has a clear hint about what they're\n1785\t    looking at.\n1786\t- Role gating: the route falls under the default `PEEK_DEFAULT_ROUTE_ROLES`\n1787\t  (business + admin) — no explicit prefix rule needed because the round\n1788\t  detail isn't admin-only. `/audit` remains the only admin-gated prefix in\n1789