-033.log\n1508\t\n1509\t\n1510\t\n1511\t## Iteration 34 — 2026-04-25\n1512\t\n1513\t- FR-8 frontend half: the `/games/[game]` route. One Next.js dynamic\n1514\t  segment that resolves `flipyou`, `potshot`, and `closecall` and\n1515\t  notFounds anything else (validated against `PEEK_GAME_IDS`). Page is\n1516\t  role-gated through `getPeekActorContext` + `isRouteAllowedForRole`\n1517\t  the same way `/games` is, so unknown roles render the existing\n1518\t  access-denied alert without leaking the table.\n1519\t- Two server-side branches inside the page:\n1520\t  - FlipYou + Pot Shot share `listRounds({ game })` and render\n1521\t    `GameRoundsTable`. The `[game]` param is statically narrowed to\n1522\t    `'flipyou' | 'potshot'` before the call so TypeScript enforces the\n1523\t    `PeekRoundsGameId` constraint introduced in iteration 33; Close\n1524\t    Call cannot be passed to `listRounds` even by accident.\n1525\t  - Close Call calls `listCloseCallRounds()` and renders\n1526\t    `CloseCallRoundsTable`. Different table because the column set\n1527\t    (open/close prices, expo, green/red pools, total fee, outcome) and\n1528\t    the lifecycle (`open` -> `settled`/`refunded`) differ from the\n1529\t    shared `rounds` table.\n1530\t- New `peek/src/lib/games-search-params.ts`:\n1531\t  - `normalizeRoundFiltersFromSearchParams` produces a\n1532\t    `PeekRoundFilters` from raw Next.js search params (`phase`,\n1533\t    `search`, `fromDate`, `toDate`, plus the four stuck booleans\n1534\t    `stuckAged`, `stuckAttempts`, `stuckNoTx`, `stuckRefunds`).\n1535\t    Phase passes through only if it matches `PEEK_ROUND_PHASES` so\n1536\t    a bogus URL value falls back to \"any phase\" instead of producing\n1537\t    a SQL match-nothing filter.\n1538\t  - `normalizeCloseCallRoundFiltersFromSearchParams` mirrors the same\n1539\t    shape minus `stuckAttempts` (closecall has no settle_attempts\n1540\t    column) and adds an `outcome` field validated against\n1541\t    `PEEK_CLOSECALL_OUTCOMES`.\n1542\t  - `readPageFromSearchParams` clamps non-numeric / non-positive page\n1543\t    params to `1`. The query module already clamps server-side; this\n1544\t    keeps the link the navigation renders honest.\n1545\t  - `buildRoundsQueryString` rebuilds the query string for pagination\n1546\t    links and preserves every passthrough filter so navigating to page\n1547\t    2 does not silently drop the operator's filter state.\n1548\t- New `peek/src/components/game-rounds-filter-bar.tsx`:\n1549\t  - Discriminated-union props on the `game` literal so the same form\n1550\t    component renders the right shape for FlipYou+Pot Shot vs Close\n1551\t    Call without a runtime conditional. The `outcome` dropdown only\n1552\t    renders when `game === 'closecall'`; the `stuckAttempts` checkbox\n1553\t    only renders for FlipYou+Pot Shot. Default values are reflected\n1554\t    from the parsed filter object so the form is shareable via URL.\n1555\t  - Stuck filters render as a `<fieldset>` with a labelled\n1556\t    `<legend>` (\"Stuck-state filters\") so screen readers and inline\n1557\t    HTML inspection both make the grouping obvious.\n1558\t- New `peek/src/components/game-rounds-table.tsx`\n1559\t  (FlipYou + Pot Shot) and\n1560\t  `peek/src/components/closecall-rounds-table.tsx` (Close Call):\n1561\t  - Dense tables with columns matching the FR-8 acceptance criteria:\n1562\t    `rounds` (phase, pda, match id, creator, target slot, settle\n1563\t    attempts, settle tx, result side, winner, timestamps) and\n1564\t    `closecall_rounds` (phase, outcome, pda, prices, pools, fee,\n1565\t    settle tx, timestamps). Lamports / u64 strings format with\n1566\t    thousands separators while preserving the `\"0\"` literal for\n1567\t    measured zeros (FR-4).\n1568\t  - Phase + outcome render through the existing `StatusChip` so\n1569\t    refunded / expired / settled states pop visually without a\n1570\t    chart library; tone mapping mirrors the spec's exce