{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AvSrhVKGW7q9iQ92GRmVKd","type":"tool_result","content":"1300\t  counters; deferred games (Crash, Game of Trades, Chart the Course, Slots\n1301\t  Utopia, Tug of Earn) appear as documented placeholders only, per\n1302\t  System Invariant 13.\n1303\t- New `peek/app/games/page.tsx` — server-rendered route, `dynamic =\n1304\t  \"force-dynamic\"`. Calls `getPeekActorContext` + `isRouteAllowedForRole`\n1305\t  for the page-level access gate (the layout already does the outer gate\n1306\t  via the `AdminShell`; the page repeats the check so a no-role caller\n1307\t  still sees an `<alert>` instead of an empty data shell). Sections:\n1308\t  - **Overview** — feeds the 6-metric strip (`games.total_entries`,\n1309\t    `games.unique_users`, `games.wagered_lamports`, `games.settled_entries`,\n1310\t    `games.refund_entries`, `games.payout_lamports`) into the existing\n1311\t    `MetricStrip`. Each metric carries the FR-4 bookkeeping (label,\n1312\t    definition, source `game_entries`, window \"All time\", asOf,\n1313\t    `freshness: \"live\"`, drilldown `/games`).\n1314\t  - **Per-game activity** — renders the new `GamesOverviewTable`\n1315\t    against `overview.perGame` (3 rows, one per known `PeekGameId`,\n1316\t    zero-filled when missing).\n1317\t  - **Deferred games** — static list of the 5 deferred game labels with\n1318\t    a per-row reason (\"Phase-2 deferred; no persisted rounds table yet.\"\n1319\t    / \"Spec-only; awaiting persisted data source.\") so an operator can\n1320\t    see at a glance why no counters exist.\n1321\t- New `peek/src/components/games-overview-table.tsx` — dense readonly\n1322\t  table over `PeekGameOverviewRow`. Friendly game labels (`flipyou →\n1323\t  FlipYou`, `potshot → Pot Shot`, `closecall → Close Call`) plus the\n1324\t  raw id as a sublabel. Right-aligned numeric columns with\n1325\t  thousands-separator formatting for both lamport sums and integer\n1326\t  counts (FR-4: integer formatting for counts; lamports preserved as\n1327\t  precise underlying value via `text` columns). Empty state explains\n1328\t  `game_entries` is empty rather than rendering \"0\" rows that could be\n1329\t  mistaken for measurement; error path surfaces the load error in an\n1330\t  inline alert.\n1331\t- Page error handling mirrors `/growth/referrals`: a single failure in\n1332\t  `getGamesOverview()` populates `overviewError` and propagates to both\n1333\t  the `MetricStrip` (`error` prop) and `GamesOverviewTable` (`error`\n1334\t  prop) so a broken query alerts in both sections without blanking the\n1335\t  page.\n1336\t- The dedicated FR-8 test pair (`/games` query + page tests) is the\n1337\t  next checklist item; this iteration ships the UI scaffolding only.\n1338\t  The existing test surface (250 tests) was preserved.\n1339\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅,\n1340\t  `pnpm test --run` ✅ (250/250, no regressions), `pnpm build` ✅\n1341\t  (Next.js compiles the new `/games` route alongside `/`,\n1342\t  `/users/[userId]`, `/growth/referrals`, and `/growth/kol`).\n1343\t\n1344\t## Iteration 31 — 2026-04-25T12:50:02Z — OK\n1345\t- **Log**: iteration-031.log\n1346\t\n1347\t\n1348\t\n1349\t## Iteration 32 — 2026-04-25\n1350\t\n1351\t- FR-8 test pair for `/games`: query coverage for `getGamesOverview()`,\n1352\t  component coverage for `GamesOverviewTable`, and a small refactor to lift\n1353\t  the deferred-games placeholder list out of `app/games/page.tsx` so it can\n1354\t  be tested directly.\n1355\t- Refactor — `peek/src/lib/deferred-games.ts` (new):\n1356\t  - Exports `PEEK_DEFERRED_GAMES` (typed `ReadonlyArray<PeekDeferredGame>`)\n1357\t    and a `PeekDeferredGameId` union covering Crash, Game of Trades, Chart\n1358\t    the Course, Slots Utopia, and Tug of Earn.\n1359\t  - `app/games/page.tsx` now imports `PEEK_DEFERRED_GAMES` instead of\n1360\t    declaring the local `DEFERRED_GAMES` constant. Page render is byte-\n1361\t    identical (same labels, same reasons, same render order); only the\n1362\t    source of the constant moved. No new prop surface, no behaviour change\n1363\t    for the page itself.\n1364\t- New `peek/src/lib/__tests__/deferred-games.test.ts` (5 tests):\n1365\t  - Stable display order matches the expected 5 phase-2 ids.\n1366\t  - Every entry has a non-empty operator-readable label + reason and no\n1367\t    `undefined`/`TODO` strings leak into the UI.\n1368\t  - Deferred ids do not overlap with active `PEEK_GAME_IDS` — enforces\n1369\t    System Invariant 13 at the type level (active games own their\n1370\t    counters; deferred games are placeholders only).\n1371\t  - Crash entry is flagged as Phase-2 (the spec-distinguished case).\n1372\t  - Ids are unique.\n1373\t- New `peek/src/server/db/queries/__tests__/get-games-overview.test.ts`\n1374\t  (8 tests):\n1375\t  - Populated path: 3 games returned by SQL → 3 normalized perGame rows in\n1376\t    stable `PEEK_GAME_IDS` order, all 6 `PEEK_GAME_OVERVIEW_METRIC_IDS`\n1377\t    emitted with FR-4 bookkeeping (label, definition, source\n1378\t    `game_entries`, windowLabel \"All time\", asOf, freshness `live`,\n1379\t    drilldownHref `/games`). Cross-game totals are sanity-checked against\n1380\t    the per-game inputs (entries, settled, refund, wagered, payout).\n1381\t    Asserts the unique-players metric reads the platform-wide DISTINCT\n1382\t    count rather than naively summing per-game distincts (would double-\n1383\t    count a player who played multiple games — the iteration 30 design\n1384\t    note). Asserts the SQL emits the per-game GROUP BY + the FILTER\n1385\t    clauses for refund detection (`is_winner is null`).\n1386\t  - Sparse (no rows): both queries return zero, the per-game table still\n1387\t    zero-fills every `PEEK_GAME_ID`, and the metric strip emits all 6\n1388\t    metrics with `0`/`\"0\"` values rather than dropping the strip.\n1389\t  - Sparse (one game only): a single populated game row coexists with\n1390\t    zero-filled siblings; cross-game totals equal the populated row.\n1391\t  - String count coercion: postgres ::text counts (e.g. `\"9\"`) parse to\n1392\t    real numbers in the view model.\n1393\t  - Unknown game ids: a bogus `\"crash\"` row from the DB is filtered by the\n1394\t    `PEEK_GAME_IDS` allowlist so deferred/out-of-band rows cannot leak\n1395\t    into the UI or distort totals.\n1396\t  - BigInt sum precision: two near-MAX_SAFE_INTEGER lamport sums add to\n1397\t    `\"18014398509481984\"` (Number addition would round) — verifies the\n1398\t    `BigInt`-based `sumLamports()` chosen in iteration 30.\n1399\t  - Load error (aggregate): a rejected per-game query propagates so the\n1400\t    page can render the alert state.\n1401\t  - Load error (DISTINCT count): a rejected unique-users query also\n1402\t    propagates.\n1403\t- New `peek/src/components/__tests__/games-overview-table.test.tsx`\n1404\t  (4 tests):\n1405\t  - Populated: all 9 columns render (Game, Entries, Unique users,\n1406\t    Wagered (lamports), Settled, Refunds, Paid out (lamports), Wins,\n1407\t    Losses); friendly labels (`FlipYou` / `Pot Shot` / `Close Call`) sit\n1408\t    next to the raw id sublabels (`· flipyou` etc.); thousands-separator\n1409\t    formatting applies to both counts and lamports; `\"0\"` stays bare.\n1410\t  - Zero-filled row: a fully-zero per-game row renders literal `\"0\"`\n1411\t    across all 8 numeric cells (preserves measured-zero semantics — FR-4\n1412\t    forbids em-dashes for measured zeros).\n1413\t  - Empty state: `rows={[]}` renders the operator status block pointing\n1414\t    at `game_entries`; no `<table>` element rendered.\n1415\t  - Error state: an `error` prop renders the alert and suppresses both\n1416\t    the table and the empty status.\n1417\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm test --run` ✅ (267/267, +17 from\n1418\t  iteration 31's 250), `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅.\n1419\t## Iteration 32 — 2026-